  8  /-!
  9  # Floor and Ceil
 10  
 11  ## Summary
 12  
 13  We define `floor`, `ceil`, and `nat_ceil` functions on linear ordered rings.
 14  
 15  ## Main Definitions
 16  
 17  - `floor_ring` is a linear ordered ring with floor function.
 18  - `floor x` is the greatest integer `z` such that `z ≤ x`.
 19  - `fract x` is the fractional part of x, that is `x - floor x`.
 20  - `ceil x` is the smallest integer `z` such that `x ≤ z`.
 21  - `nat_ceil x` is the smallest nonnegative integer `n` with `x ≤ n`.
 22  
 23  ## Notations
 24  
 25  - `⌊x⌋` is `floor x`.
 26  - `⌈x⌉` is `ceil x`.
 27  
 28  ## Tags
 29  
 30  rounding
 31  -/
 32  
 33  variables {α : Type*}
 34  
 35  /--
 36  A `floor_ring` is a linear ordered ring over `α` with a function
 37  `floor : α → ℤ` satisfying `∀ (z : ℤ) (x : α), z ≤ floor x ↔ (z : α) ≤ x)`.
